Investment Services & Portfolio Management




Company Description


SusGlobal Energy Canada Corp. acquires and develops alternative energy technologies. It provides a full range of services for handling organic residuals in a period where innovation and sustainability are paramount. The firm's technology solutions include anaerobic digestion and mixed waste plastics to diesel. It uses process source separated organics in anerobic digestors to divert from landfills and recover biogas, This biogas can be converted to gaseous fuel for industrial processes, electricity to the grid, and cleaned for compressed renewable gas. The company was founded by Gerald P. Hamaliuk and Marc M. Hazout and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.




Website


http://www.susglobalenergy.com






